  "body": "### User Story\r\n1. As a **User** I want to send a message, but forgot something so I navigate to other options like discovery, contacts etc. & come back again to type the message, but Edit box is not cleared. It's displaying previous message on Edit box, even though didn't send.\r\n2. As a **Tester** I want to test that, after typing message, suppose, User goes back or navigate to other options & come back again to type the message, then Edit box is cleared & not retaining previous message.\r\n3. As a **Developer**, I need to see that, once Edit box is used(whether User is sending the message or not, Or only typing then too), & navigating to other options on User Interface ,when User comes back to same element- _Edit box, it should be automatically cleared Or typed message should automatically saved to draft._\r\n\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug.\r\n\r\n*Summary*: ...\r\n1.Sign to status.\r\n2.open chats.\r\n3.open any contact \r\n4.type a message , but don't send it.\r\n5.Go back or navigate to other options on UI - Discover, contact\r\n6.Again come back to  same contact & open.\r\n7. Notice the Edit box option on User Interface. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nShould clear automatically Edit boxes.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nNot getting cleared automatically.\r\nPlease see attached screenshot \r\n![testmsg](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20433356/33924697-3cd7bc86-dffd-11e7-8a7c-378c24e2558d.png)\r\nhttps://drive.google.com/file/d/1kTpUc4qH97jjtEtBGJNJjsZeTCMhH3kT/view\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nAfter typing the msg, _**If**_ User ( doesn't send typed message) \r\nthen,\r\nEdit box -> Clear ||  EditBox msg -> Save To Draft\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: ...\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Android 6.0.1\r\n",
